---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<style>
  .fd-cards-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 0 5rem;
  }

  .fd-card {
    flex: 1;
    flex-basis: 30%;
    background: rgba(26, 42, 69, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .fd-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.4);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.1);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }

  .fd-card-header {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.15);
    background: rgba(10, 22, 40, 0.4);
  }

  .fd-card-header :global(.fd-section-heading) {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #3ee8b5;
  }

  .fd-card-body {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    flex-grow: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .fd-card-body :global(.fd-paragraph) {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #e8e4df;
  }

  .fd-card-body :global(.fd-list) {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .fd-card-body :global(.fd-list-item) {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #e8e4df;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .fd-code-block {
    background: rgba(10, 22, 40, 0.8);
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.15);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #a8d8c8;
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .fd-examples-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .fd-examples-table thead tr {
    background: rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.12);
  }

  .fd-examples-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem;
    color: #3ee8b5;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.25);
  }

  .fd-examples-table td {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    color: #e8e4df;
    line-height: 1.6;
    vertical-align: top;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.08);
  }

  .fd-examples-table td:first-child {
    white-space: nowrap;
    width: 22%;
    color: #c8ddd5;
  }

  .fd-examples-table tbody tr:nth-child(odd) {
    background: rgba(26, 42, 69, 0.5);
  }

  .fd-examples-table tbody tr:nth-child(even) {
    background: rgba(10, 22, 40, 0.4);
  }

  .fd-examples-table tbody tr:hover {
    background: rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.06);
  }

  .fd-decision-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .fd-decision-panel {
    background: rgba(26, 42, 69, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .fd-decision-panel h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #3ee8b5;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .fd-decision-panel :global(.fd-list) {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .fd-decision-panel :global(.fd-list-item) {
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    color: #e8e4df;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .fd-steps {
    counter-reset: step-counter;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .fd-step {
    counter-increment: step-counter;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .fd-step::before {
    content: counter(step-counter);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.75rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    background: rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 232, 181, 0.4);
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #3ee8b5;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .fd-step-content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .fd-step-content strong {
    display: block;
    color: #e8e4df;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .fd-step-content span {
    color: #a8b8c8;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>

<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Not every care process needs a complex, formal workflow. When work is repetitive and stateless — the same action repeated across many independent entities — Machina uses <strong>informal tasks</strong>: lightweight workflows that can contain many activities to be performed by multiple people. 
</p>

<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Imagine a patient is being discharged after a minor outpatient procedure. There's no rigid, system-enforced workflow for this — it's just a series of handoffs between team members to make sure nothing falls through the cracks.
</p>

<figure class="fd-inline-figure">
  <img
    src={`${base}/visualizations/informal-workflow.png`}
    alt="An informal workflow with three activities that must be completed to close the task"
    class="fd-inline-img"
    style="width: 700px;"
    loading="lazy"
  />
</figure>

<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Each task sits in a queue. A specialist grabs one, performs the action, advances the queue status, and releases it. No blocks, no summaries, no transition logic — just a task with extra state.
</p>

<div class="fd-cards-container">

  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Lightweight by design</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        Informal tasks skip the full workflow pipeline — no blocks, summaries, or transition logic. When you have 500 facilities to contact, creating 500 full workflow tasks would be wasteful. Informal tasks keep the workflow engine lean.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Queue-native</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        Built for lock → act → release work. A specialist locks a task, performs an action (send fax, make call, file document), updates the queue status, and releases. The backing table tracks progression without workflow-level state accumulation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="fd-card">
    <div class="fd-card-header">
      <h2 class="fd-section-heading">Full audit trail</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="fd-card-body">
      <p class="fd-paragraph">
        Like all workflow tasks, informal tasks create assignment periods and queue status periods — a complete record of who worked on what and when. The backing table stores additional domain-specific details: attempt dates, file references, notes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>


<h2 class="fd-section-heading">Choosing the right tool</h2>

<div class="fd-decision-grid">
  <div class="fd-decision-panel">
    <h3>Informal tasks are the right fit when</h3>
    <ul class="fd-list">
      <li class="fd-list-item">When an ad hoc series of activities need to be performed aren't standard business operations</li>
      <li class="fd-list-item">Each activity is independent—they don't need to be performed in any particular order</li>
      <li class="fd-list-item">You need a record of what happened, but not a complex decision trail</li>
      <li class="fd-list-item">Speed and volume matter more than official processes</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fd-decision-panel">
    <h3>Full workflows are the right fit when</h3>
    <ul class="fd-list">
      <li class="fd-list-item">Care has distinct phases and what happens next depends on what came before</li>
      <li class="fd-list-item">Different outcomes require different follow-up paths</li>
      <li class="fd-list-item">You need a structured record of decisions made along the way</li>
      <li class="fd-list-item">The patient journey itself — not just a single task — is what you're managing</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">Real-world examples</h2>
<table class="fd-examples-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Use case</th>
      <th>How it works</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Patient Complaint Resolution</strong></td>
      <td>A patient calls in upset about a long wait time during their last visit and a billing charge they weren't expecting. No formal grievance process is triggered — it's not that serious — but the practice wants to make sure it gets handled thoughtfully.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Credentialing and Onboarding</strong></td>
      <td>A new physician assistant has been hired, and several people across the organization need to chip in to get them fully onboarded. There's no single system driving this end to end — it's a collaborative effort that moves between departments as each piece gets handled.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Medical Equipment Repair Request</strong></td>
      <td>When meeting with a patient in their home, a representative notices that a portable vital signs monitor intermittently dropping readings and isn't reliable enough to keep using. It's not an emergency — there are other units available — but it needs to get handled before it becomes a bigger problem.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
